	<key>readme</key>
	<string># OmniFocus Collection

A collection of Alfred actions demonstrating the integration of Omni Automation with Alfred. Detailed explanation and documentation is provided on the [Omni Automation website](https://omni-automation.com/alfred)

---

### REQUIREMENTS:

NOTE: All Alfred actions in the collection currently require OmniFocus to be active or running in the background.

Prior to running the actions:

- In the OmniFocus application, enable the “Accept scripts from external applications” preference in the “Security” tab of the “Automation Configuration” dialog, accessed by selecting the “Automation” menu &gt; “Configure…” menu option.

During the use of the actions:

The execution of any external Omni Automation script will cause the display of a Script Security Window.

- In the security dialog, fully scroll the Omni Automation script to review it, and then approve its execution by pressing the “Run Script” button at the bottom right of the window.

- IMPORTANT: To enable the script to run without subsequent re-approval, select the checkbox located at the bottom left labeled “Automatically run this script when sent by Alfred”. Once the preference is selected and the script is run, a security window will no longer be presented for this workflow.

- The “List OmniFocus Projects” and “List OmniFocus Tags” actions rely upon Apple Events and so require user approval of the system security dialog shown during their initial execution.

---

## Example Actions

Here are the example Alfred actions:

### Select 1st Inbox Item

This action will switch the current view in OmniFocus to the Inbox and select the first item.

### New Sequential Project

This action will create and select a new sequential project titled using the name entered in Alfred.

### Smart Search OmniFocus Projects

This action will use the entered search terms to display a linked list of the matching projects in Alfred.

### Tasks Due Today

This action will display a linked list in Alfred of the OmniFocus taks due today. NOTE: With the installation of the included Voice Control commands file, this action can be triggered using a Voice Control command.

### List OmniFocus Projects

This action will display a linked list of all OmniFocus projects in Alfred. Select a list item to display it within OmniFocus.

### List OmniFocus Tags

This action will display a linked list of all OmniFocus tags in Alfred. Select a list item to display it within OmniFocus.</string>
